{"type":"message","id":"735e8740","parentId":"848cae6d","timestamp":"2026-04-10T16:49:58.986Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No existing memory about wiki/knowledge base. Let me check my workspace to see if there's anything already set up. Let me also understand my current context better by checking the workspace structure.\n\nThe user wants me to:\n1. 全面认真学习 - Fully study and learn\n2. 进行思考 - Think about it\n3. 基于自身情况 - Based on my own situation\n\nMy situation:\n- I'm OpenClaw, an AI assistant\n- My workspace is `/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace`\n- I already have MEMORY.md, AGENTS.md, SOUL.md, IDENTITY.md, USER.md, TOOLS.md, HEARTBEAT.md - these ARE essentially a personal wiki schema!\n- There's a memory system already in place\n\nThis is a meta request - they want me to think about how to apply this LLM Wiki pattern to MY own setup/operation.\n\nLet me analyze this deeply:\n\n**My Current \"Wiki\" Infrastructure:**\n1. MEMORY.md - This IS an index of my knowledge\n2. memory/*.md - Structured knowledge modules\n3. AGENTS.md - Schema/workflow definitions\n4. SOUL.md - Persona and behavior constraints\n5. IDENTITY.md - Self-definition\n6. USER.md - User profile/preferences\n7. HEARTBEAT.md - Operational config\n\nThis is ALREADY a form of LLM Wiki! The user is essentially asking me to recognize this and think about how to improve it or apply the pattern more deliberately.\n\nLet me also check if there's anything in the workspace directory.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_d929ca26814d4568a2b0baa3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"codingplan","model":"minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":21503,"output":351,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21854,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775839794267,"respons