{"type":"message","id":"bbc0f0a8","parentId":"fe97208e","timestamp":"2026-04-10T17:14:58.194Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me think through more carefully what might still be missing based on the original LLM Wiki document:\n\n1. **Contradiction tracking** - The doc says \"noting where new data contradicts old claims\" - I have this in lint but should make it more prominent\n\n2. **Claim strength** - \"strengthening or challenging the evolving synthesis\" - not explicitly handled\n\n3. **Output formats** - The doc mentions: markdown page, comparison table, slide deck (Marp), chart (matplotlib), canvas. I mentioned Marp in Obsidian but not the full output format strategy.\n\n4. **Human's role** - The doc explicitly says \"The human's job is to curate sources, direct the analysis, ask good questions, and think about what it all means. The LLM's job is everything else.\" This is a key philosophical point I should capture.\n\n5. **Memex reference** - Vannevar Bush's vision - worth adding as context\n\n6. **The compounding nature** - The doc emphasizes \"The wiki keeps getting richer with every source you add and every question you ask\" - this mindset should be reinforced\n\n7. **The workflow detail** - \"I have the LLM agent open on one side and Obsidian open on the other\" - this practical setup should be documented\n\n8. **Weekly/monthly maintenance** - The lint says weekly/monthly but doesn't specify what exactly\n\n9. **Cross-reference maintenance** - \"The LLM updates relevant entity and concept pages across the wiki\" - this automatic propagation isn't fully automated\n\n10. **Source curation** - The human's job to select what goes into raw/\n\nLet me add these missing pieces.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n对照原文再深挖：\n\n## 🔍 遗漏检查\n\n| 原文要点 | 现状 | 动作 |\n|----------|------|------|\n| **矛盾标记** — \"noting where new data contradicts old claims\" | lint 有提到，不具体 | 增强 |\n| **Claim 强弱** — \"strengthening or challenging the synthesis\" | 无 | 新增 |\n| **输出格式** — 表格、幻灯片、图表 | 提了 Marp，不完整 | 增强 |\n| **人之职责** — \"curate sources, ask good questions\" | 无专属页 | 新增 |\n| **Memex 引用** — Vannevar Bush 1945 | 无 | 新增 |\n| **实时双屏** — \"LLM on one side, Obsidian on other\" | 无 | 新增 |\n| **每周维护** — 具体做什么 | 模糊 | 增强 |\n\n补全：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_1d1ebe0c1eb642809e2cd5c0","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"---\ntitle: Human Role\ntype: concept\nstatus: active\nlast_updated: 2026-04-11\ntags: [human-role, curation, strategy]\n---\n\n# 👤 Human Role\n\n> 人在 LLM Wiki 中的职责\n\n## 核心理念\n\n> \"The human's job is to curate sources, direct the analysis, ask good questions, and think about what it all means. The LLM's job is everything else.\"\n\n— LLM Wiki Pattern\n\n---\n\n## 人的职责\n\n| 职责 | 说明 | 示例 |\n|------|------|------|\n| **精选来源** | 什么值得放入 raw/ | 高质量文章、论文、笔记 |\n| **方向引导** | 分析目标是什么 | \"我想了解 X 领域\" |\n| **提问** | 问好问题是关键 | \"X 和 Y 有什么异同？\" |\n| **思考总结** | 连接点、意义 | \"这说明什么？\" |\n\n## LLM 的职责\n\n| 职责 | 说明 |\n|------|------|\n| 读取与提取 | 从原始文档中抽取要点 |\n| 维护更新 | 写页面、改链接、更新矛盾 |\n| 跨引用 | 建立页面间的连接 |\n| 例行检查 | 每周 lint、健康检查 |\n\n---\n\n## 协作模式\n\n```\n┌─────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐\n│   你 (人)        │     │   LLM (我)       │\n├─────────────────┤     ├─────────────────┤\n│ 放入 raw/       │ ←── │ 读取源文件       │\n│ 提问/分析目标   │ ──→ │ 提取要点         │\n│ 思考 + 追问     │ ←── │ 合成答案         │\n│ 决定是否写回    │ ──→ │ 更新 wiki        │\n└─────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## 实践建议\n\n1. **不要** 让 LLM 读所有东西 → 只读精选的\n2. **多问** 开放性问题 → \"X 是什么？\", \"X 和 Y 有什么不同？\"\n3. **好的答案** → 主动写回 wiki\n4. **定期** → 打开 Obsidian 看看 wiki 长什么样\n\n---\n\n## 相关页面\n\n- [[llm-wiki]] — 模式概念\n- [[ingest]] — 知识摄取\n\n---\n\n*最后更新：2026-04-11*","path":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/memory/entities/human-role.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"codingplan","model":"minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":52734,"output":1083,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":53817,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775841283300,"responseId":"chatcmpl-bf4ba057-29ee-4705-82dc-6c8ba88a3263"}}
